## 4. Technical Requirements

### Data Model
The app needs to store and manage the following data:

**Users:**
- email, display name, avatar, role (user/admin), creation date

{% for block in blocks %}
**{{ block.name }}:**
- title, description, status (active/draft/archived), owner (user reference)
{% if block.category | default("feature") == "data" %}
- Additional structured data fields, tags
{% endif %}
- Timestamps (created, updated)

{% endfor %}

### Core Functionality
- **CRUD Operations:** Create, read, update, and delete for each feature block.
- **Authentication:** User registration and login with secure password handling.
- **Authorization:** Users can only access and modify their own data.
- **Pagination:** Lists should paginate at 20 items per page.
- **Search / Filter:** Users should be able to search by title and filter by status.
- **Form Validation:** Client-side validation on all input forms with clear error messages.
- **Loading States:** Show loading indicators during data fetches.
- **Error Handling:** Display user-friendly error messages, never raw error codes.

### API Structure
